Sure! To write an if/then statement in C, you need to use the if keyword followed by a condition enclosed in parentheses. If the condition is true, the statement or block of code after the if keyword will be executed. Here's an example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
  printf("You are eligible to vote.");
}
```

In this example, if the age variable is equal to or greater than 18, the statement inside the if block will be executed, and the user will see the message "You are eligible to vote."
